<def f='qtbase-6.5.0/src/widgets/graphicsview/qgraphicsscene.cpp' l='2173' ll='2176' type='void QGraphicsScene::setSelectionArea(const QPainterPath &amp; path, const QTransform &amp; deviceTransform)'/>
<doc f='qtbase-6.5.0/src/widgets/graphicsview/qgraphicsscene.cpp' l='2158'>/*!
    \since 4.6

    Sets the selection area to \a path. All items within this area are
    immediately selected, and all items outside are unselected. You can get
    the list of all selected items by calling selectedItems().

    \a deviceTransform is the transformation that applies to the view, and needs to
    be provided if the scene contains items that ignore transformations.

    For an item to be selected, it must be marked as \e selectable
    (QGraphicsItem::ItemIsSelectable).

    \sa clearSelection(), selectionArea()
*/</doc>
